hopobject.body: Could you give me some smaller notes? www.netcaremedicalscheme.co.za Gross the chief of the division of sports medicine and the orthopedic director at Hackensack University Medical Center, said in multiple interviews with media outlets that he did not see any indication of injury on the MRI. Gross, however, had been reprimanded in February by the New Jersey Attorney General for "failing to adequately supervise proper patient treatment involving the prescription of hormones including steroids." New Jersey officials said Gross had allowed an unlicensed associate participate in the care and treatment of patients.
